{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01C6feAtq7FDCou5qTSYHRDv","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Vector Databases\n2\t\n3\tA vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search.\n4\t\n5\t## Popular Options\n6\t\n7\t- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n8\t- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n9\t- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n10\t- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n11\t\n12\t## How They Work\n13\t\n14\t1. Documents are converted to embeddings using a model\n15\t2. Embeddings are indexed for fast nearest-neighbor search\n16\t3. At query time, the query is embedded and compared to stored vectors\n17\t4. The most similar vectors (and their associated documents) are returned\n18\t\n19\t## Use Cases\n20\t\n21\t- [RAG systems](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) for grounding LLM responses\n22\t- Semantic search across large document collections\n23\t- Recommendation engines\n24\t- Image and audio similarity search\n25\t\n26\t## Sources\n27\t\n28\t- sources/vector-databases.md\n29\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aeb2d5e5-49d7-48c0-8570-3ae359065cfe","uuid":"cb22412b-b78b-42c6-ab9e-1485503e573c","timestamp":"2026-07-09T15:36:08.970Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-databases.md","content":"# Vector Databases\n\nA vector database stores data as high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) and enables fast similarity search. They are a key component in [RAG](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) pipelines, recommendation systems, and semantic search.\n\n## Popular Options\n\n- **ChromaDB** — open-source, easy to set up, Python-native\n- **Pinecone** — managed service, scales automatically\n- **Weaviate** — open-source, supports hybrid search (vector + keyword)\n- **Qdrant** — open-source, Rust-based, high performance\n\n## How They Work\n\n1. Documents are converted to embeddings using a model\n2. Embeddings are indexed for fast nearest-neighbor search\n3. At query time, the query is embedded and compared to stored vectors\n4. The most similar vectors (and their associated documents) are returned\n\n## Use Cases\n\n- [RAG systems](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) for grounding LLM responses\n- Semantic search across large document collections\n- Recommendation engines\n- Image and audio similarity search\n\n## Sources\n\n- sources/vector-databases.md\n","numLines":29,"startLine":1,"totalLines":29}}}
