{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01BDEuEuDivgpXgqtMgci1cG", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "Now I have all the information I need. Let me:\n\n1. Create the `vector-similarity-search.md` wiki page\n2. Add back-links to `vector-databases.md` and `retrieval-augmented-generation.md` in their Related sections\n3. Update `index.md` with the new page\n4. Update `log.md` with an entry\n\nI notice that neither `vector-databases.md` nor `retrieval-augmented-generation.md` have a \"Related\" section - they both end with \"Sources\". I'll need to add Related sections to them.\n\nFor the new page, the connections I see:\n- `vector-databases.md` implements similarity search as their core function\n- `retrieval-augmented-generation.md` relies on vector similarity search for its retrieval step\n- `agent-eval-harness.md` could use embedding similarity for deduplication, which ties to an active project\n\nLooking at the index structure, there's no existing \"Machine Learning\" or \"AI Techniques\" category yet, so I need to figure out where this fits best. I should create a new \"Machine Learning & AI\" category in the index and add the Vector Similarity Search page there, though I could also include the existing vector-databases.md and retrieval-augmented-generation.md files for consistency. Now I'm starting to write out the new page content.", "signature": ""}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1808, "cache_read_input_tokens": 38577, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1808, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "aeb2d5e5-49d7-48c0-8570-3ae359065cfe", "uuid": "660aca68-c96e-4a2f-a9ff-32f499b1ee8a", "request_id": "req_vrtx_011CcrjKmUE98rLbbAb1LEJU", "timestamp": "2026-07-09T15:36:27.798Z"}
