{"type": "assistant", "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_vrtx_01BDEuEuDivgpXgqtMgci1cG", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "tool_use", "id": "toolu_vrtx_015PPKecT6EkZ6QCh4jaPacq", "name": "Write", "input": {"file_path": "/Users/ejaquez/second-brain/wiki/vector-similarity-search.md", "content": "# Vector Similarity Search\n\nCore technique for finding semantically similar content using vector embeddings \u2014 the engine behind modern search, recommendations, and deduplication.\n\n## Key Points\n\n- Text is transformed into dense vector embeddings via transformer models (e.g. OpenAI, Cohere, sentence-transformers)\n- Similarity measured with cosine similarity (angle between vectors) or dot product (magnitude-aware)\n- Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) algorithms trade small accuracy losses for large speed gains\n  - **HNSW** (Hierarchical Navigable Small Worlds) \u2014 graph-based, best recall/speed trade-off\n  - **IVF** (Inverted File Index) \u2014 cluster-based, efficient at massive scale\n- Exact search is O(n) per query; ANN brings this closer to O(log n)\n- Powers: RAG retrieval, recommendation engines, semantic search, duplicate detection\n\n## Related\n\n- [Vector Databases](vector-databases.md) \u2014 specialized stores that implement ANN indexing at scale\n- [Retrieval-Augmented Generation](retrieval-augmented-generation.md) \u2014 uses vector similarity as its retrieval step\n- [Agent Eval Harness](agent-eval-harness.md) \u2014 similarity search is applicable for deduplicating test cases and detecting redundant eval inputs\n\n## Sources\n\n- Ingested: 2026-07-09\n"}}], "stop_reason": null, "stop_sequence": null, "stop_details": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 1, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 1808, "cache_read_input_tokens": 38577, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 1808, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 8}, "context_management": null}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "ae